How many marks do you need to become a pilot?
You’ll be surprised — the answer is simple.

✅ All you need are passing marks in Physics and Maths in 12th grade — that’s it.

You don’t need a 90% board result. You don’t need to be a topper.
What you do need is clarity, consistency, and a clear flight plan.

If you’re dreaming to fly — make sure you walk the right path. Ask questions. Don’t fall for paid glamour. Trust those who’ve truly lived this life.

How much does it really cost to become a pilot? Let’s break it down. ✈️💸 I will help you! 

Becoming a pilot is more than just a dream—it’s a serious investment. And the first step to turning that dream into reality? Planning your budget smartly.

From your first ground school class to your final flight hours, everything comes with a cost:
📍 Training fees (different for CPL, PPL, type ratings, etc.)
📍 Accommodation & living expenses (especially if you train away from home)
📍 Medical tests, uniforms, study material, and licenses
📍 Travel costs, food, and emergency reserves

It’s not just about how much—but also how well you plan. With proper guidance and a realistic budget, the journey becomes smoother and more focused.

🎯 This reel breaks down where your money goes and how to plan ahead.

✈️ Thinking of becoming a pilot?
